 services** provided by a Musk‑owned company.\n   - **Equipment leases and subleases** with Valor Equity Partners (affiliated with board member Antonio J. Gracias).\n\n   These transactions are eliminated because they occurred among entities under common control, even though the disclosure often uses Tesla and other affiliates as examples.\n\n### Treatment in the Consolidated Statements\n- The **capital stock and shareholders’ equity** are presented as a continuation of SpaceX’s historical equity combined with the equity of X and xAI, adjusted for the exchange ratios used in the mergers.\n- The **redeemable convertible preferred stock** of xAI is presented separately until its conversion into SpaceX common stock upon the xAI merger, and then recognized prospectively in Q1 2026.\n\n### Summary\nIn essence, the prospectus emphasizes that because all three entities were under common control, **any transactions among them—including revenue, costs, loans, leases, or service agreements—are treated as if they never occurred for consolidation purposes and are thus fully eliminated**. This ensures the financial statements present the combined entity as a single reporting unit from the earliest period presented.',
