e **pre-merger, standalone financial statements of xAI and X Holdings**. The SpaceX prospectus presents combined historicals where these transactions are eliminated.\n2.  **Grok Integration Costs:** These are not broken out as a specific line item. They would be subsumed within the **AI segment\'s Research and Development expenses** (for model development) and potentially **Cost of Revenue** (for infrastructure and operational costs to support the integration).\n3.  **Specific Intercompany Service Agreements:** The terms of these agreements are not detailed in the provided excerpts. The narrative focuses on the accounting treatment that renders their financial impact neutral in the consolidated statements.\n\nIn summary, the financial statements do not disclose the specific intercompany flows because common-control accounting requires their elimination. The nature of the services is described in the revenue recognition and business overview sections, but their historical financial impact is presented as a net zero within the consolidated results.',
